    "text": "Transcriptome profiling from 1 to 25 dpa reveals dynamic gene expression pathways. These pathways shift from cellular growth and embryo development (1–5 dpa) to cell division, fatty acid biosynthesis (5–25 dpa), and seed storage compounds synthesis in the endosperm (5–25 dpa). Network analysis identifies 361 hub genes linked to starch synthesis in the endosperm and 207 hub genes linked to protein synthesis in the endosperm. This will help breeders enhance sorghum grain quality.",
